Description: AquaBlok is a manufactures and distributes composite (clay-based) materials.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: AquaBlok, Ltd. manufactures and distributes composite (clay-based) materials. It offers sediment remediation products, such as low permeability and thin capping management tools for the containment and treatment of contamination in sediments; a family of bentonite well sealant and grout materials to seal and aid in pollution prevention; wetland restoration products, including composite-aggregate materials; and materials for various geotechnical applications.  The company also provides algae and pond management products, which include products that utilize dense aggregate (limestone) core to deliver naturally mined bentonite clay through a water column to various areas where a leak is suspected; and an orthophosphate removal product to clarify ponds, lakes, and other waterways. It offers its products for use as a low permeability capping material to isolate contaminated sediments; a means to improve the performance of organoclay and other amendment materials for in situ treatment of contamination in aquatic settings; a nutrient management tool and water clarifier; and a leak prevention and repair sealant-effective during and after construction. The company also provides its products for use as an annular sealant/grout material in well construction and well abandonment; a seed delivery alternative for wetland plant restoration; a levee repair or dam reinforcement in flood control applications; and an anti-seep collar (or ‘plug’) for pipes, control structures, and other underground installations. It offers its products through a network of sales representatives/distributors in Seymour, Indiana; Apopka, Oakland Park, and Titusville, Florida; St. Paul, Minnesota; Bowling Green, Ohio; Grant, Michigan; Curtice, Ohio; Singapore; Birmingham, Alabama; and Lexington, Kentucky, as well as distributes its products globally. The company was incorporated in 1999 and is based in Toledo, Ohio.

Full Description: Hammer and Grind is a clothing brand specifically targeting the new generation of motorcycle riders who grew up in the action sports community. My background is as an entrepreneur. I have owned a skateshop and skate brand called Fake Skateboards, an In-door skate park, A large screen printing plant Airship Printing, my wife and I own a hipster knitting brand called ""Knerd"" that is really taking off after it's first trade show. Description: Appraisal Economics is an independent valuation company that has performed thousands of appraisals for a diverse range of clients.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Appraisal Economics is an independent business valuation company that has performed thousands of appraisals over more than 25 years. Our clients range from multi-billion dollar publicly traded companies with diverse operations to privately held, early stage companies. Often, we are engaged by law firms or private equity firms on behalf of their clients or portfolio companies. We also serve government agencies and not-for-profits. Our individual clients have included a Nobel Prize-winning economist, a former United States Secretary of the Treasury, entrepreneurs, philanthropists, and many small business owners. Appraisal Economics have appraised business interests and assets worldwide and even the rights to satellite orbit paths in outer space. We offer a range of services including: business valuations, complex securities valuations, intangible asset studies, goodwill impairment studies, trademark and patent valuations, real estate appraisals, and machinery and equipment valuations. We provide appraisal services for accounting, tax, litigation, and transaction-related purposes.  Appraisal Economic's team members have graduated from some of the best universities and have gained unique experiences from assignments around the world. We also participate in rigorous continuing education programs because we recognize that staying at the top of our field requires continual growth and development. Some members of our team have been issued a U.S. patent, held the position of chief financial officer, and achieved other high-level accomplishments before joining Appraisal Economics. Our members hold designations and credentials from organizations such as the American Society of Appraisers, the American Institute of CPAs, the CFA Institute, and various real estate licensing boards. Appraisal Economic's team regularly serves in officer positions for the American Society of Appraisers. Our team has authored numerous articles and lectured extensively on valuation topics, including intellectual property and power plants. We also have extensive experience providing expert witness testimony in federal, state, and tax courts, at arbitration hearings, and at Federal Communication Commission hearings. Many members of our staff have received U.S. government security clearance through the Internal Revenue Service background investigation process. This enables them to work on projects of an extremely sensitive nature. Today we have an experienced team of appraisers, accountants, economists, and engineers that have both a deep understanding of common and complex appraisal issues, and diversified real-world experience across many industries. Our wide-ranging backgrounds and experiences allow us to view projects from multiple perspectives and deliver the best possible service to our clients. Appraisal Economics would consider it a privilege to serve you. If you need a valuation for accounting, tax, transaction, litigation, or planning purposes, please contact us.

Description: Go2marine sells and delivers boat parts and marine supplies worldwide with a focus on stop-at-nothing customer service and fast shipping.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The combining of Go2marine and the LFS Marine & Outdoor websites in 2019 effectively increased our company’s internet presence and ability to provide you with the goods and services you need to enjoy boating and the outdoors or tackle your commercial endeavor. LFS was founded in 1967 as an outfitter and supplier to commercial fishing operations in the Pacific Northwest. Note-worthy expertise and a high quality of service allowed LFS retail stores to grow and diversify. By combining our two stores, we are able to extend our retail offerings to include sport fishing goods, pleasure boating parts and supplies, sports netting, marine engine parts, recreational outdoor supplies and commercial good and services. Bellingham locationGo2marine has shipped to boaters in over 175 countries since the year 2000. Our beginning focus was on suppling marine products to commercial fishing vessels, pleasure boaters and getting the do-it-yourself boater the parts needed to get the job done right. To do this, Go2marine was founded by seasoned boaters and is still staffed by experienced boaters and marine engine mechanics. We continue to meet those goals and expanded our online store as the years progressed. In 2016, we joined with LFS Marine & Outdoor to continue meeting the needs of boaters all over the world. The LFS Marine & Outdoor retail store is located on Coho Way, in the heart of the marina district in beautiful Bellingham, WA. Please be aware that this website, is a separate division of LFS, Inc. and that online pricing and selection may differ from that available in store. In addition to the LFS Marine & Outdoor retail location, LFS’s Trawl / Sport & Specialty Netting division is also located in Bellingham. The LFS Sports and Industrial Netting division specializes in custom netting solutions such as golf courses, baseball fields, and wildlife barriers. Our LFS Seattle store is in Ballard just blocks from the Fremont Cut and Lake Washington Ship Canal. Our Seattle store stands ready to serve commercial and industrial customers as well as recreational boaters With six locations in Alaska, LFS has a year-round presence in Anchorage, Cordova, Dutch Harbor, Homer (Kachemak Gear Shed), and Kenai with two seasonal locations in Dillingham and Naknek. The Go2marine online support division is located in Poulsbo, Washington not far from Liberty Bay but does not stock product. LFS remains committed to their core business of supplying and supporting the commercial marine industry as well as providing parts and gear boaters and outdoor enthusiasts worldwide. LFS’s distribution center is located in Bellingham, WA and has partnered with manufacturers and suppliers to ship from multiple locations to quickly serve every port and city in North America. You can count on LFS to get the parts you need and ship them directly to you, no matter where you are. We encourage you to join our boating community. You can create an account online and sign up for our emails to receive updates on sales and coupons. You can follow us on Facebook and Twitter to stay informed with the latest news and information on boating products and events. We strive to offer the best customer service and would love to hear from you. Please leave us your feedback and read what others are saying on our customer reviews.

Full Description: Kachuwa Impact Fund is an investment cooperative and public benefit corporation focused on owning and operating “impact real estate” and investing in privately-held “impact companies. Kachuwa is a cooperative corporation formed under Colorado law. A cooperative corporation is one that is formed for the benefit of its members, provides for one vote per member (regardless of the amount of their investment), and distributes profits on the basis of “patronage” – which generally means the amount of business done with the cooperative. As a cooperative, Kachuwa is democratically owned and controlled by its members. By design, at least 60% of Kachuwa’s assets are real estate and no more than 40% of its assets are investments.
